The paper deals with distributed algorithms in computer networks, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The problem of backup placement involves selecting neighbors in a network, which is related to the sub-category of Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the neighborhood independence of graphs, which is a topic in Structural Information Theory (cs.SI). The algorithms presented in the paper involve approximation and optimization, which are topics in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of distributed symmetry breaking problems, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT).
